'''Hussein Haydar Hussein Ali''' ({{langx|ar|حُسَيْن عَلِيّ}}; born 1 March 2002) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for [[Ekstraklasa]] club [[Pogoń Szczecin]].<ref name="SW">{{Soccerway|hussein-ali/573309}}</ref> Born in Sweden, he plays for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Malmö]], [[Sweden]], Hussein Ali was trained by his hometown club, the [[Malmö FF]], but did not play any matches for the first team. In August 2019, at the age of 17, he joined [[Örebro SK]],<ref>{{cite web|date=13 August 2019 |language=sv |title=Officiellt: ÖSK värvar försvarare från MFF |url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/allsvenskan/officiellt-osk-varvar-forsvarare-fran-mff/ |website=www.fotbollskanalen.se}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> and made this choice because of the strong competition in Malmö and considering that he would have more chances in Örebro.<ref>{{cite web|date=16 November 2020 |language=sv |title=Ali har slagit igenom i Örebro |url=https://www.allsvenskan.se/nyheter/nyheter-fran-allsvenskan.se/ali-har-slagit-igenom-i-orebro |website=www.allsvenskan.se}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref> He made his first professional appearance for Örebro in a [[Allsvenskan]] match against [[IFK Norrköping]] on 21 September 2019.

On 19 July 2022, Ali joined [[Eredivisie]] side [[SC Heerenveen|Heerenveen]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Heerenveen|url=https://www.sc-heerenveen.nl/nieuws/2022/sc-heerenveen-legt-hussein-ali-vast-tot-2025|title=SC HEERENVEEN LEGT HUSSEIN ALI VAST TOT 2025|date=19 July 2022|access-date=20 July 2022|language=nl}}</ref>

On 18 September 2025, Ali signed a three-year deal with [[Ekstraklasa]] club [[Pogoń Szczecin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Hussein Ali nowym piłkarzem Pogoni Szczecin. Reprezentant Iraku podpisał kontrakt |url=https://szczecin.tvp.pl/89001091/hussein-ali-w-pogoni-szczecin-reprezentant-iraku-podpisal-trzyletni-kontrakt |website=szczecin.tvp.pl |access-date=18 September 2025 |language=pl |date=18 September 2025 |trans-title=Hussein Ali is a new Pogoń Szczecin player. The Iraqi international has signed a contract}}</ref>

==International career==
Ali represented Sweden at youth international level.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=van der Meeren |first=Peter |date=26 August 2023 |title=Hussein Ali, de Zweed van Heerenveen die voor Irak gaat spelen, wil voorbeeld zijn. 'Volg je hart en denk groot' |url=https://lc.nl/sport/Durf-te-dromen-28608042.html |access-date=28 August 2023 |website=[[Leeuwarder Courant]] |language=nl-NL}}</ref>

In August 2023, he officially switched allegiances to Iraq, and received his first call-up to the [[Iraq national football team|senior national team]] for the [[2023 King's Cup]].<ref name=":0" />

He was one of twenty-six Iraqi players selected by [[Jesús Casas]] to compete in the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|date=10 January 2024 |language=en |title=Iraq Is One Of The Strong Teams In Group D Of The 2023 Asian Cup Which Is The First Opponent Of The Indonesian National Team |url=https://voi.id/en/sports/346553 |website=voi.id}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

== Personal life ==
Born in [[Sweden]], Ali is of [[Iraq]]i Arab descent.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Hussein Ali |url=https://www.sport.de/fussball/pe567049/hussein-ali/ |website=sport.de}}</ref>

